The paper focuses on the security and privacy of Internet of Drones (IoD), which involves the processing of sensitive and mission-critical information. This suggests that the paper belongs to the category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper addresses the energy constraints of IoD, which implies that it could also belong to the categories of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) and Systems and Control (cs.SY). The paper proposes an energy-efficient cryptographic framework, which involves the integration and optimization of key exchange, digital signature, and public key encryption schemes. This suggests that the paper could also belong to the categories of Software Engineering (cs.SE) and Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC).
